  "decision": {
    "hot_helper_feature_read": "The MBS1/MBS2/MBS4/MBS8 ladder robustly establishes the MindSpeed-style top-8 hot-helper feature: it improves tok/GPU/s at every fitting MBS, saves memory at MBS1-4, and moves the fit boundary so MBS8 is usable while no-helper MBS8 fails.",
    "needed_weight_layout_read": "The opt-in owner-compact needed exchange plan is functionally valid but not a performance path. A 3-step smoke was misleadingly close to selected layout, but the 20-step late window is 27.6% slower and 13.8 GiB higher-memory than the selected-layout hot-helper reference.",
    "primus_turbo_vs_mori": "Continue native MORI balanced-MoE as the main path. Primus-Turbo TurboEPBackend remains a bounded side probe only for raw top-k/no-helper EP because it does not consume the winning hot/cold/helper owner-compact partition directly.",
    "next_native_mori_target": "Do not keep adapting hot-helper onto a dense selected/needed weight ABI. Preserve the standard-EP owner-compact partition and make MORI consume/produce that compact-row layout directly for normal dispatch/combine, helper rows, dX/dTopK return, and hot dW reduction."
